sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Eventlog Clear or Configuration Change
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects clearing or configuration of eventlogs using wevtutil, powershell and wmic. Might be used by ransomwares during the attack (seen by NotPetya and others).

T1071.description: Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.
Downloads files from webservers via HTTP

T1071.001.description: Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols associated with web traffic to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.

T1106.description: Adversaries may interact with the native OS application programming interface (API) to execute behaviors.

T1129.description: The process attempted to dynamically load a malicious function
The process tried to load dynamically one or more functions.

T1057.description: The process has tried to detect the debugger probing the use of page guards.
The process attempted to detect a running debugger using common APIs
Queries a list of all running processes

T1027.009.description: The process has executed a dropped binary
Drops interesting files and uses them

T1091.description: Checks for available system drives (often done to infect USB drives)

T1059.description: Very long cmdline option found, this is very uncommon (may be encrypted or packed)
Uses cmd line tools excessively to alter registry or file data

T1569.002.description: Uses sc.exe to modify the status of services

T1543.003.description: Uses sc.exe to modify the status of services

T1547.001.description: Stores files to the Windows startup directory

T1055.description: Injects a PE file into a foreign processes
Modifies the context of a thread in another process (thread injection)
Hijacks the control flow in another process

T1562.001.description: Creates guard pages, often used to prevent reverse engineering and debugging
Disables security and backup related services

T1070.004.description: May delete shadow drive data (may be related to ransomware)

T1036.description: Creates files inside the user directory

T1497.description: May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis

T1564.001.description: Creates files in the recycle bin to hide itself

T1056.description: Installs a raw input device (often for capturing keystrokes)
